1. Explain how constructors and destructors can be used in your project.
- Constructor: sets the product’s ID, name, and price when the object is created. It also prints a message showing the object was created.
- Destructor: runs automatically when the object is no longer needed. It prints a message showing the object was destroyed.

2. What similarities do the class, constructor, and destructor share?
- All belong to the same class.
- All help manage the object’s lifecycle.
- Constructors and destructors have the same name as the class.
- Constructors and destructors do not have a return type.

3. Expected output of the program.


